==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Hindi]] [[पट्टी]] (''paṭṭī'') (a bandage, strip of cloth) ➤ [[Sanskrit]] [[पट्टिका]] (''paṭṭikā'') of similar meaning.

====References====
*McGregor, R.S, ed. ''The Oxford Hindi-English Dictionary'', Oxford university press. 1993
*Platts, John T. ''[http://dsal.uchicago.edu/dictionaries/platts/ A dictionary of Urdu, Classical Hindi, and English]'' Oxford. 1884.
*Cappeller, Carl  ''[http://www.uni-koeln.de/phil-fak/indologie/tamil/cap_search.html A Sanskrit-English dictionary]''  Bostin, Ginn and Co., 1891.

===Noun===
'''puttee'''
# A strip of cloth wound round the leg for protection.
# [[legging]].
